      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism acts as a necessary glue for social cohesion by fostering a shared identity and motivating citizens to protect their sovereignty against external threats. Without this unifying bond, countries would likely fracture into mere loose collections of individuals unable to mobilize effectively for defense or infrastructure. Ultimately, nationalism isn't inherently dangerous but becomes a tyrannical force only when it is weaponized to suppress internal dissent or glorify the state above human rights.",
